data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_ReviewUnprotectSheetDescription
data.value:
Prevent unwanted changes to the data in a sheet by specifying what information can be edited.
For example, you can prevent people from editing locked cells or changing the formatting of the document.
You can specify a password that can be entered to unprotect the sheet and allow these changes.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_ReviewUnprotectWorkbookDescription
data.value:
Prevent unwanted changes to the structure of the workbook, such as moving, deleting, or adding sheets.
You can specify a password that can be entered to unprotect the workbook and allow these changes.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_ShowDetailCommandDescription
data.value: Expand a collapsed group of cells.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_ShowInsertSheetCellsFormDescription
data.value:
Add new rows, columns, cells, or sheets to workbook.
New rows will be added above the selection and new columns will be added to the left of the selection.
Add three columns at once by selecting three existing columns first; this also works for multiple rows.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_ShowNameManagerDescription
data.value:
Create, edit, delete, and find all the names used in the workbook.
Names can be used in formulas as substitutes for cell references.
For example: =SUM(Sales) instead of =SUM(C20:C30).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_SortAscendingDescription
data.value: Sort the selection so that the lowest values are at the top of the column.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_SortDescendingDescription
data.value: Sort the selection so that the highest values are at the top of the column.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_SubtotalCommandDescription
data.value: Calculate rows of related data by automatically inserting subtotals and totals for the selected cells.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_TableToolsConvertToRangeDescription
data.value:

All of the data is preserved.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_TableToolsRenameTableCommandDescription
data.value: Edit the name of this table used to refer to it in formulas.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_TableToolsToggleBandedColumnsCommandDescription
data.value:
Display banded columns, in which even columns are formatted differently from odd columns.
This banding can make tables easier to read.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_TableToolsToggleBandedRowsCommandDescription
data.value:
Display banded rows, in which even rows are formatted differently from odd rows.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_TableToolsToggleFirstColumnCommandDescription
data.value: Display special formatting for the first column of the table.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_TableToolsToggleHeaderRowCommandDescription
data.value:

A header row formats the top row of the table specially.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_TableToolsToggleLastColumnCommandDescription

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_TableToolsToggleTotalRowCommandDescription
data.value:
Turn on or off the total row of the table.
The total row is the row at the end of the table which displays totals for each column.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_ToggleCellLockedDescription
data.value:
Lock the selected cells to keep people from making changes to them.
You must turn on Protect Sheet in order for this feature to work.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_UngroupCommandDescription

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_ViewShowFormulasDescription
data.value: Display the formula in each cell instead of the resulting value.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_ViewShowGridlinesDescription
data.value: Show the lines between rows and columns in the sheet to make editing and reading easier.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetStringId.MenuCmd_ViewShowHeadingsDescription
data.value:
Show row and column headings.
Row headings are the row numbers to the side of the sheet.
Column headings are the letters or numbers that appear above the columns on a sheet.
